By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) – Governor Muhammadu Inuwa Yahaya of Gombe state has expressed sadness over the demise of a frontline politician, business man and chieftain of the All Progressives Congress, APC Alhaji Adamu Yaro Gombe, popularly known as AY Gombe, who died yesterday. Governor Yahaya in a statement signed by his Senior Special Assistant  (Media and Publicity), Ismaila Uba Misilli, described the deceased as a strong political figure, pillar, community leader and philanthropist, who impacted positively on the lives of many. He recalled the late Alhaji AY Gombe’s support and valuable contributions to the All Progressives Congress, APC in the state both in the build-up to the 2019 general election and during the transition period where he served as member of the Information and Publicity Sectoral Committee. The Governor said, ” I am Deeply shocked and saddened to learn about the sudden demise of this respected gentleman. His death is a personal loss to me both as an ally and a good neighbour of many years. AY Gombe was indeed an exceptional man and illustrious son who contributed tremendously to the development of Gombe state and left an indelible mark in the annals of the state”. “On behalf of the Government and people of Gombe state, I extend my heartfelt condolences to his family, friends and associates over this huge loss”. “I pray Almighty Allah to forgive his shortcomings and grant him Aljannat Firdaus”. Similarly, Governor Inuwa Yahaya has extended his deep condolences to the family of the late Hon. Sa’idu Jaudoma and the entire people of Dukku over the demise of the former state lawmaker, praying Allah to comfort his family with the fortitude to bear the loss and grant the deceased Aljannat Firdaus. 